to long for/to wish/to cling to/to stick to/sth that sticks/close to/next to/spread open/informal abbr. for bus 巴士[ba1 shi4]/bar (unit of pressure)/nominalizing suffix on certain nouns, such as 尾巴[wei3 ba5], tail

sentences.english: Objective To study the formation mechanism of diaphragmatic lymph in rats.
sentences.chinese: 目的探討大鼠膈淋巴液形成的機制。

sentences.english: This law can promote lymphatic fluid and haemal circulation, improve bosom nutrition metabolization.
sentences.chinese: 此法可促進淋巴液及血液循環，改善胸部營養代謝。

sentences.english: Methods The method of the drainage of lymph fluid was well established.
sentences.chinese: 建立並熟練掌握大鼠腸淋巴液引流的方法。

sentences.english: It also improves immune regulation by pumping lymphatic fluid back into the blood.
sentences.chinese: 它也提高了回血抽淋巴液的免疫調節作用。

sentences.english: You have three times more lymphatic fluid in your body than you do blood.
sentences.chinese: 人體中所含淋巴液是血液的三倍。
